  "notes": "Acehnese (Basa Acèh / Acèh), Malayo-Polynesian language of Aceh, Sumatra. Latin orthography (1980 standard, replacing the earlier Husaini/Dutch-based spelling); the Jawoë (Arabic-derived) script is also traditionally used and is NOT modelled here — input is assumed to be in the Latin orthography. Ten oral vowel qualities; nasal vowels are written with a preceding apostrophe and are not enumerated as separate graphemes here. Word-final ⟨k⟩ is realised as a glottal stop.",
